[
    {
        "content": "<p>Is there any way to tell lean to show all the implicit arguments in an error message?<br>\nFor example, sometimes when rewrite fails, I would want to know if there are different implicit args that caused the rewrite to fail</p>",
        "id": 154824603,
        "sender_full_name": "petercommand",
        "timestamp": 1547109827
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Or in a type mismatch error</p>",
        "id": 154824649,
        "sender_full_name": "petercommand",
        "timestamp": 1547109847
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Sometimes it shows all the implicit arguments sometimes it doesn't</p>",
        "id": 154824655,
        "sender_full_name": "petercommand",
        "timestamp": 1547109864
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>set_option pp.all true</code> will show you everything... that might be too much though...</p>",
        "id": 154824659,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1547109871
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>set_option pp.implicit true</code> before the declaration.</p>",
        "id": 154824660,
        "sender_full_name": "Rob Lewis",
        "timestamp": 1547109874
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Aah, there you go.</p>",
        "id": 154824663,
